    "title": "Reality Vector: Environmental State Representation for Constrained AI Systems",
    "publication_date": "2026-04-24",
    "description": "Reality Vector defines the formal mechanism by which intelligent systems maintain a bounded, accurate representation of external environmental state. Rather than unbounded world models, Reality Vectors encode only the constraint-relevant subset of environmental parameters, updated via constrained sensor feeds with explicit uncertainty bounds. This paper provides the mathematical formalism, update semantics, and environmental intelligence modeling framework for bounded reality representation.",
